LinkedInData:
{'summary': 'Cory has spent 30 years in the restaurant industry, in one form or another. Historically an entrepreneur, Cory has built and sold five businesses over that time, only to start anew with an increased excitement and vigor. 
Most note-worthy, previous business endeavors include Accurate Chemical, sold in 2004, now a thriving juggernaut serving the restaurant industry throughout the southwest and Remington Restaurant Equipment Repair, sold in 2012. Successful in that industry approach, the current business venture is Alpha & Omega Restaurant Equipment Repair founded in 2015. Yates and co-owner Edgar Martinez, lead technician for Alpha & Omega, seek to fill the gap between the larger, but less responsive, less communicative companies and the unlicensed, uninsured “fix-it-all” guy.
The theory for Cory is to be customer centric. “Bend when you need to and give back to those who trust you with their own livelihood. Build relationships based on that trust and typically, all the results take care of themselves".
Steady growth and a solid reputation for an unparalleled customer experience, industry revered skills, teamwork and accurate communication are, and always will be Alpha & Omega’s goals. While other companies strive to be the largest or "fastest growing" in Arizona, Alpha & Omega Restaurant Equipment Repair strives to remain the very best.', 'industryName': 'Restaurants', 'lastName': {'summary': 'I’ve been a part of the Due North, Minus Forty team for over 30 years. We passionately develop innovative refrigeration merchandising products and solutions to fulfill our customers’ requirements. Our products range from single and double glass door models, to countertop and undercounter specialty models.

With a proven track record as COO at Due North, my goal is to further expand our brand and market reach. We deliver state-of-the-art products and exceptional customer service through the leading and coaching of our team members, developing and demonstrating core company values, and successfully maintaining a positive and prosperous working environment. Our success is built on our team’s desire to exceed expectations and finding innovative solutions for our customers.

Our North American-made freezers and coolers provide superior product life and presentation. We are as invested in our customers’ bottom lines as they are. When they choose us, we go the extra mile to help them market more effectively and sell more. We do this through our approach and understanding of technology, presentation and customized merchandising designs that have an immediate buying impact.

Our customers range from the major food giants, grocery stores, convenience and gas stations, commercial produce, retail, cafeterias and micro markets to ice cream vendors.

{'summary': 'I am an experienced business leader that believes that inspiring people with shared values can create fantastic business results. I’ve been fortunate to have learned and applied processes like DMAIC and Six Sigma to optimize supply chain, manufacturing performance and operational excellence. My BS in Mechanical Engineering from Iowa State University gave me a good start, and I continue to learn by embracing the next challenge or opportunity.

In my current role, I lead a merged corporate entity of QBD and Minus Forty, commercial refrigeration manufacturers. We are a dominant player in the beverage, micro market, pet food and retail categories. The combined business has world-class technology, excellent talent and some very innovative IoT smart technology. 

Driving business value for our shareholders means continuing to exceed the demands of our customers. {'summary': 'I’m the Global CEO of Flexeserve, world-leading hot-holding manufacturer, hot food-to-go specialist and proud recipient of two Queen’s Awards for Innovation. We partner with and support global retailers and independent outlets, helping them sell more and waste less.

Our achievements belong to our entire team. We’re incredibly passionate about advancing the world of food-to-go and feel a shared responsibility to our customers to drive development within the industry. It’s deeply fulfilling to see sustainable, efficient and exciting hot food programs around the world that have only been made possible with our equipment and expertise.

We’re innovators through and through – developing our hot-holding units in direct response to operator needs. For example, our Queen’s Award-winning flagship product, Flexeserve Zone enables retailers to offer a diverse range of hot food from a small footprint with minimal resources. It can do this because it’s the world’s only heated display capable of accurately maintaining multiple air temperatures in one unit.

Flexeserve is a brand of The Alan Nuttall Partnership, a company I joined in 1995. I’ve worked in every area of this business and, today, I maintain a hands-on approach with all aspects of Flexeserve. My unique understanding of our brand and its potential has helped shape my strong vision for Flexeserve, driving our progress and exponential year-on-year sales growth.

‘The first and still the best’ - in 1996, we discovered that convection was the only way to truly keep hot food at optimum quality and temperature. Back then, we were well ahead of the game and now, we change it, continually refining how best to use our technology. I was inspired by our hot-holding units – and the potential they unlocked for our customers – to establish a clear competitive edge in the marketplace.

Flexeserve Solution is the industry’s only hot-holding service. Our in-house team of world experts helps customers unlock transformational benefits: reduced food waste, extended shelf life, amazing food quality, diverse food range, unmatched efficiency and happier consumers.

As global demand for our equipment and expertise has increased, I’m spearheading our transatlantic growth strategy, establishing Flexeserve Inc. to support customers across the Americas. This will transform the way American operators serve and sell hot food. We’re in the process of establishing our North American HQ in Southlake (Dallas) TX, launching in Summer 2023.

LinkedInData:
{'summary': 'Hi, I’m Director of Customer Experience for Flexeserve, a brand of The Alan Nuttall Partnership. My role covers our range of Flexeserve products, including the award-winning Flexeserve Zone.

Flexeserve Zone is the industry-leading, patented hot-holding solution, capable of maintaining a wide variety of foods at optimum serving conditions for record hold times. It enables food outlets to improve their hot food-to-go offering, eliminate waste and maximise sales.
 
As Director of Customer Experience, I’m involved in every element of our customers’ interface with Flexeserve and responsible for the sales, marketing and culinary support areas of the Flexeserve brand. I ensure that all of our customers have the best possible experience of our unique Flexeserve Solution. 

I’m actively involved in the development of our marketing strategy. This includes collaborating with our creative agency on marketing materials and online presence. These provide you with a range of informative content, not just on Flexeserve but on the general benefits and opportunities of hot food-to-go. 

Along with my experience in working with customers to find the best tailored solutions for their hot-holding needs, I’m also responsible for our sales team, helping to deliver comprehensive advice to make well-informed decisions. As a company, we are changing the preconceptions of hot-holding and pushing the boundaries of what can be achieved.

I originally joined Flexeserve as Development Chef and have been pivotal in developing the customer experience into what it is today. I’ve also built relationships with key partners in food packaging and manufacturing to create a complete solution for end users.

Flexeserve Zone is not just a heated display, it’s a comprehensive hot-holding solution. The results achieved are the product of the great work done by our team of hot food-to-go experts.

{'summary': "VENTILATION SOLUTIONS YOU CAN TRUST TO MEET CODE
Most home builders are struggling to meet the stringent ventilation requirements in the latest energy codes without exceeding their budget. 

WHAT I DO: I am working with the top builders, contractors, and energy raters in the industry to develop a unique alliance program to make it easy and affordable to meet the stringent new ventilation requirements found in the latest energy codes. 

WHO I WORK WITH: 
•	Single-Family Home Builders
•	Energy Raters
•	HVAC & Electrical Contractors
•	Offsite Construction

WHY IT WORKS: Our new program can assist in designing cost-effective ventilation systems that meet the latest IECC standards and help qualify for the 45L Federal Tax Credit. 

WHAT MAKES US DIFFERENT: We can achieve this by utilizing advanced ventilation fans, ERVs, and a unique business approach. In contrast to residential-grade alternatives, our products offer code compliant verified performance, and we provide design support through an exclusive network of Energy Rater Partners. 

HOW IT WORKS:
If you are ready to achieve easy, cost-effective code compliance, the process is simple:
 1. We have a quick 30-minute meeting to discuss your code requirements, ventilation design goals, and procurement objectives.
 2. We work with all your stakeholders, our partners, and you to create a customized solution and purchasing program to ensure everyone succeeds.
 3. If everything looks good, we'll implement the program, so code compliance is no longer a concern.

READY TO TALK?
